# [Project Title]

## 1. Business Task
Clearly describe the question or problem the project addresses and why it is important.

## 2. Data Source
Provide a short description of the dataset:
- Source and licensing
- Structure and size
- Relevant fields
- Why the dataset is appropriate for the problem

## 3. Data Cleaning and Preparation
Document the main steps taken to clean and prepare the data:
- Removing duplicates
- Handling missing values
- Standardizing formats
- Creating new variables
- Filtering out invalid records
- Tools used (SQL, R, spreadsheets, etc.)

## 4. Analysis
Describe the methods used to explore and analyze the data:
- Key metrics
- Comparisons
- Trends
- Visualizations
- Code or queries used (summaries only, full scripts can be included in an appendix)

## 5. Key Findings
Summarize the most important insights discovered in the analysis.

## 6. Recommendations
Provide recommendations based on the findings. These should be practical, realistic, and connected directly to the insights.
